SENATE BILL DRS45477-MTa-183
Short Title: Pay Teachers What They're Worth Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Bradley (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO INCREASE EDUCATOR SALARIES, TO REINSTATE EDUCATION-BASED
3 SALARY SUPPLEMENTS FOR EDUCATORS, TO ESTABLISH THE PAID STUDENT
4 TEACHING GRANT PROGRAM, AND TO REQUIRE THE NORTH CAROLINA
5 COLLABORATORY TO STUDY IMPROVING EDUCATOR COMPENSATION.
6 Whereas, North Carolina continues to experience teacher shortages in multiple
7 subject areas and geographic regions; and
8 Whereas, student teaching is a full-time professional requirement that often prevents
9 teacher candidates from maintaining outside employment; and
10 Whereas, financial barriers during clinical preparation discourage many prospective
11 educators from entering the profession; and
12 Whereas, competitive salaries and stronger teacher preparation pipelines are essential
13 to ensuring that North Carolina students have access to qualified teachers; and
14 Whereas, the purpose of the following enactment is to strengthen recruitment and
15 retention of educators by improving compensation and supporting teacher candidates entering
16 the profession; Now, therefore,
17 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
18
19 PART I. RAISE SALARIES FOR TEACHERS AND INSTRUCTIONAL SUPPORT
20 PERSONNEL
21 SECTION 1.(a) The following monthly teacher salary schedule shall apply for the
22 2026-2027 fiscal year to licensed personnel of the public schools who are classified as teachers.
23 The salary schedule is based on years of teaching experience.
